  <title>New variety of apple discovered by Wiltshire runner</title>
  <slug>new-variety-of-apple</slug>
  <pubDate>2020-11-30T19:31:24.822Z</pubDate>
  <lastModified>2020-11-30T19:34:22.921Z</lastModified>
  <excerpt>Archie Thomas stumbled across solitary windfall fruit that could be cross between cultivated apple and European crab apple</excerpt>
  <content>&lt;div class="css-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i83" style="margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 36.25rem; color: #3f3f42;" data-component="text-block"&gt;
&lt;div class="css-83cqas-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;Archie Thomas, from the Nadder Valley in Wiltshire, came across across a windfall apple on a wooded trackway near his home earlier this month.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="css-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i83" style="margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 36.25rem; color: #3f3f42;" data-component="text-block"&gt;
&lt;div class="css-83cqas-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;Experts have confirmed the "highly unusual" fruit, which "tastes quite good", is a new variety, which Mr Thomas hopes to propagate and name.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="css-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i83" style="margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 36.25rem; color: #3f3f42;" data-component="text-block"&gt;
&lt;div class="css-83cqas-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;"It is unlike any apple I'd seen before," he said.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="css-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i83" style="margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 36.25rem; color: #3f3f42;" data-component="text-block"&gt;
&lt;div class="css-83cqas-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;Mr Thomas, who works for wild plant and fungi conservation charity Plantlife, said the fruit came from a lone old apple tree in a hedgerow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="css-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i83" style="margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 36.25rem; color: #3f3f42;" data-component="text-block"&gt;
&lt;div class="css-83cqas-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;img src="/Posts/files/new-variety_apple_637423614848846733.jpg" alt="new-variety_apple.jpg" width="800" height="800" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;"While I am certainly no fruit expert, it immediately struck me as highly unusual, unlike any apple I'd seen before," he said.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="css-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i83" style="margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 36.25rem; color: #3f3f42;" data-component="text-block"&gt;
&lt;div class="css-83cqas-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;"Excited by the pale and mottled oddity, I set about trying to get it identified with a view to perhaps one day being able to name it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="css-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i83" style="margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 36.25rem; color: #3f3f42;" data-component="text-block"&gt;
&lt;div class="css-83cqas-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;"That was the dream, but I did half suspect it would turn out to be something&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;much less exciting than it is."&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;After what he described as a &amp;ldquo;wild apple chase&amp;rdquo;, with many fruit experts flummoxed by the find, he received help from Plantlife colleagues and was then pointed towards the Royal Horticultural Society fruit identification service at RHS Wisley.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;The RHS fruit specialist Jim Arbury inspected three of the apples and informed Thomas it was not a planted cultivar, but a new variety that he could propagate and name.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;Arbury said it was &amp;ldquo;a very interesting apple&amp;rdquo;. It is clearly not a planted tree, but a seedling that could be a cross between a cultivated apple and a wild Malus sylvestris, a European crab apple, he said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;Archie Thomas holding a new variety of apple he discovered on a wooded trackway.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;Archie Thomas holding a new variety of apple he discovered on a wooded trackway. Photograph: Hannah Thomas/PA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;It tastes quite good. It&amp;rsquo;s a cooking apple or dual purpose, you can eat it, it&amp;rsquo;s got a bit of acidity but it&amp;rsquo;s got some flavour, and some tannin, which is what you have in cider apples,&amp;rdquo; he said, adding it could be used with other apples for cider.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;He said most chance apple trees were from Bramley&amp;rsquo;s Seedling cooking apples grown in gardens or orchards, or sometimes from supermarket apples thrown out of car windows and now growing alongside roads.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;But he said the apples sent by Thomas came from a tree that could be 100 years old or more and was not the result of a dropped modern supermarket apple.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;Thomas admitted he may be biased, but said he thought the apples tasted great. &amp;ldquo;Tart but not wincingly-so, and with enough sweetness to eat raw &amp;hellip; They speak of the terrain of Wiltshire; unimproved chalk grassland and chalk streams.,&amp;rdquo; he added.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;As for the name, Thomas said he feft pressure to get it right: &amp;ldquo;I have too many ideas. My seven-year-old son wants me to call it Cristiano Ronaldo but that&amp;rsquo;s not happening. My wife, Hannah, is the apple of my eye, so she&amp;rsquo;s in contention.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;Dr Trevor Dines, at botanical specialist at Plantlife, said: &amp;ldquo;Archie has joined a small and select group of people that have discovered something entirely new in our natural world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #3f3f42; font-family: ReithSans, Helvetica, Arial, freesans, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;I absolutely adore apples and Archie&amp;rsquo;s new find is breathtaking. And what a romantic origin, unearthed deep in a wood with ancient roots. We can only speculate how it arose, but that&amp;rsquo;s the joy of botany &amp;ndash; you never quite know what you&amp;rsquo;ll find, or how it got there. These sort of mysteries only serve to deepen our love of the countryside.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="css-38z03z" style="color: #121212; font-family: GuardianTextEgyptian, 'Guardian Text Egyptian Web', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.0625rem; font-style: inherit; font-variant-ligatures: common-ligatures; font-variant-caps: inherit; font-weight: inherit; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.5; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</content>
